THIS weekend we celebrate Heritage Day and if you are ready to enjoy a braai in warm weather with loved ones, here’s a simple warm potato salad recipe for all to enjoy. POTATO SALAD INGREDIENTS   , 1,5kg small potatoes if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>  , Few sprigs thyme   , Two tablespoons olive oilSALSA INGREDIENTS   , Two red peppers   , Three large cloves garlic, unpeeled   , One large red chilli   , Three tablespoons olive oil, extra for drizzling   , 250g tomatoes, roughly chopped   , Four spring onions, thinly sliced   , Zest and juice of one lime PREPARATION Heat oven to 200°C. Put potatoes, thyme and oil on baking tray. Season, then roast for one hour or until tender and golden.Put peppers, garlic and chilli on a small baking tray, drizzle with oil and roast in the oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.Remove the skin from the garlic and discard the stalks and seeds from peppers and chilli. Blend the peppers, garlic, chilli, a third of the tomatoes and olive oil in a food processor, then mix in the rest of the tomatoes. Add the spring onions, lime zest and juice, and serve over the potatoes.